main event: A UFO sighting was reported on 7/11/1955 approximately 50 miles southeast of Sacramento, California.
interesting points: The sighting involved one object, similar in appearance to an F-86 fighter aircraft., The object approached at a high rate of speed without producing any sound., The observation was recorded through both ground radar and air visual methods., The duration of the sighting was one minute., The conclusion suggested that the sighting might be attributed to a failed weather balloon from Beales AFB.
sighted object: one object similar to an F-86 fighter aircraft
